<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=665849" target="top">Clothes of the Day</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elrociam>Elrociam </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Leader of the Eternal Pull</span><br>  Posts: 425<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/29/03 8:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Am I a bad friend?</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with the two who have posted already.  The onus wasn't only on you to stay in contact, but your friends as well.  <br>
<br>
I have lost touch with all my high skool friends accept one.  And we speak rarely, but we know that if something were to come up, that the other would be there for them.<br>
<br>
You should not feel bad that you weren't kept in the loop. <p>The not so silent monk from the House Valiant</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=antoinnolouj>AntoinNolouj</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.personal.psu.edu/btk120/antoin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/29/03 5:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Am I a bad friend?</span><hr size=1> Girl from my high school died in February.  Penn State gave her a postmortem degree last month (May).  She sat in front of me in spanish class.  Didn't like me much, but perhaps it was understandable.<br>
<br>
How did I find out?  Buddy of mine also from high school, junior class when I graduated, emailed me since he works for the local paper, asking for information about her since he couldn't get much out of the family.<br>
<br>
I wrote back...first line in my email...<br>
<br>
&quot;Shit, she died?&quot;<br>
<br>
I had no idea.  A lot of people who go to college and also went to high school here break off and make their own friends.<br>
<br>
Guess it's time to organize a little H.S. 5th year reunion.<br>
<br>
 <p>--Captain Antoin Nolouj<br>
Shadowknight of 52 Opponents</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zadonz>ZadonZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/29/03 7:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Am I a bad friend?</span><hr size=1> Define 'Friend'.  Was he really a friend if you had no contact with him?  I would count him as an 'old friend' or 'former friend' whom you speak with rarely.  If you had no contact with him, you can't really say you were a friend to him at all (presently anyhow).  <br>
<br>
I'm not at all critisizing...just making a point.  To me this is no big deal simply because the contact wasn't there.  Remember communication goes 2-ways.  If he didn't make the effort to contact you for such a long time, I'm sure he had other people around him to fill the spot you used to be in.  You've done nothing wrong and you should not feel bad about this.<br>
<br>
Feel a little sad that he is gone.  Remember any good ideas or thoughts that he may have brought into your life.  Move on with a clear consience.<br>
<br>
