<br>
Then September 11 happened, and I and all of his other friends who keep in touch online were worried about him, but he popped up a couple days after the fact to let us know he was all right; he'd actually had a job interview scheduled in the second tower that morning, but he'd overslept and missed it. Freak chance. That's the sort of thing that just gives you chills.<br>
<br>
Then in late December he stopped logging on. We assumed at first he was just busy with the holidays, then we figured he must have gotten a new job that was keeping him busy (he'd had long periods of inactivity like that before). No one really worried about him; we just figured he'd pop up again eventually and we'd all give him shit for being a stranger. The following July his mother finally managed to get in touch with a few of us to let us know he'd been murdered. <br>
<br>
I cried all day.<br>
